text.tspan: Pelican Pt appears to be providing sustained PFR.
The unit first responds to frequency drop, then
ramps down to respond to over-frequency.
Pelican Point was cleared for same energy target
for DI 13:10, DI 13:15, DI 13:30. Consistent
power output whilst frequency increases beyond
upper NOFB suggests control settings maintain
droop response.
Osborne is operating with no headroom, so no
response to under-frequency. Downward response
could be withdrawn PFR, with sampling error
obscuring full response (as per Stanwell responses)
North Brow, Hallett1 and The Bluff rapidly reduce
output, with the latter two reducing to zero output.
AEMO report said 4 windfarms in SA reduced output
to zero due to an incorrect protection setting - all
4 have the same turbine models. The Bluff appears
to increase output in stages despite over-frequency.
Other wind farms with foot room do not appear to
demonstrably respond to over-frequency
(e.g. Hornsdale, Hallett 2, Snowtown)
Providing sustained PFR. As outlined in AEMO
report, Bungala operating without headroom,
so no response expected for under-frequency.
Immediate response and followinf reduction in
output following disturbance consistent with GPS.
Based on AEMO data, response was 1s after
frequency had already peaked.
